1#!/usr/bin/env perl
2
3# Import geo-coding data into an SQLite database.
4
5# Software copyright 2020-2024 Nigel Horne.
6
7# Except for the "known_places" database, all the databases are copyrighted by third parties.
8#       I've tried my best to acknowledge that, but if I haven't please let me know.
9
10# The program code is released under the following licence: GPL2 for personal use on a single computer.
11# All other users (including Commercial, Charity, Educational, Government)
12# must apply in writing for a licence for use from Nigel Horne at <njh at nigelhorne.com>.
13
14# -f:   force a build, otherwise it won't build on CPAN smokers or if the
15#       database already exists
16
17# Set OSM_HOME, OPENADDR_HOME, DR5HN_HOME and WHOSONFIRST_HOME to the directories where the data will be downloaded
18
19# see bin/download_databases which will download the databases and call this script
20
21# Download the OPENADDR_HOME data from http://results.openaddresses.io.
22#       cd $OPENADDR_HOME
23#       wget --quiet https://data.openaddresses.io/openaddr-collected-global.zip
24#       wget --quiet https://data.openaddresses.io/openaddr-collected-global-sa.zip
25# or
26#       wget -nc --quiet https://s3.amazonaws.com/data.openaddresses.io/openaddr-collected-global.zip
27#       wget -nc --quiet https://s3.amazonaws.com/data.openaddresses.io/openaddr-collected-global-sa.zip
28#       unzip openaddr-collected-global.zip
29#       unzip openaddr-collected-global-sa.zip
30# Remove all the data you're not going to use, I only keep au, ca, us
31#       echo ?? | sed 's/ /\n/g' | egrep -v '(au|ca|us)' | xargs rm -rf
32#       rm -rf summary
33
34# Download the WHOSONFIRST_HOME data from repositories such as
35#       https://github.com/whosonfirst-data/whosonfirst-data-venue-us.git
36#       I use whosonfirst-data-[venue|admin]-[au|gb|us|ca].git
37#       I use whosonfirst-data-[venue]-us-??.git
38
39# Download the DR5HN database:
40#       cd $DR5HN_HOME && git clone https://github.com/dr5hn/countries-states-cities-database.git
41
42# Openstreetmap.org data
43#       cd $OSM_HOME && /usr/bin/wget https://download.geofabrik.de/europe-latest.osm.bz2
44# Note that this can take a day to load in just AU, CA, GB, US
45
46# You can look up a WOF place at https://spelunker.whosonfirst.org/id/$locality_id
47#
48# Try:
49#       sqlite3 whosonfirst-data-latest.db
50#       select body from geojson where body like '%north shields%';
51# It'll be slow, but it shows the sort of thing this is about,
52#       You'll see an id: field (e.g. 1108937103), then look at
53#       https://spelunker.whosonfirst.org/id/1108937103
54
55# TODO: perhaps use a layered approach to the database schema
56# TODO: import https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dr5hn/countries-states-cities-database/master/countries%2Bstates%2Bcities.json
57# TODO: as the database is a simple key/value pair, perhaps CDB will be better
58
